{"word":"ἑδώλιον","slug":"ἑδώλιον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἑδώλιον</b></el> <el>(ἑδώλιον, ου, τό,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἕδος'><el>ἕδος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a seat</i>, mostly in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a>, <i>abodes</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>in a ship, <el>ἑδώλια</el> are <i>the rowingbenches</i>, or rather <i>a half-deck</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}